OL,4,Chospital ward jailed
OL,6,FThe judge, Mr Justice Goss, said it
OL,7,Fwas a "difficult and troubling case"
OL,8,Fwhich was unlike any he had
OL,9,Fencountered before in his career.
OL,11,FHe said that, given Hardwick's mental
OL,12,Fdisability and "rigid thought
OL,13,Fprocess", as well as an "absence of
OL,14,Fany other possible reason for such a
OL,15,Fdramatic act", he accepted that she
OL,16,F"might have thought it was the
OL,17,Fmerciful thing to do at that time".
